\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Typewriter Scrolling\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardeftab720\sl336\slmult1\sb260\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 Typewriter mode is a special typing mode that is available on the iPad. You can turn it on by tapping the \'93T\'94 icon in the navigation bar while editing, or via the Project Settings (the gear icon in the toolbar below the binder). In this mode, the line of text you are typing remains centred on the screen, so that your eyes aren\'92t always staring at the bottom of your iPad as you write. (You can change the position of the typewriter line via Scrivener\'92s options in Settings app.)\
\
