\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 The Extended Keyboard Row\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardeftab720\sl336\slmult1\sb260\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 Above the keyboard (or at the bottom of the screen if you are using an external keyboard) you will notice that there is an extra row of keys. You can swipe left and right between three different sets of eight buttons, giving 24 in total. These provide options for punctuation, text navigation and formatting, and the keys shown here are fully customisable\'97tap and hold a button to bring up the customisation palette. You can thus set this row up to contain the commands that are most useful to you. (You can turn off the keyboard row entirely via Scrivener\'92s options in Settings app.)\
\
